name: Albino Whale Calf Breaching
description:
I paint whales to highlight the need for us to take care of our oceans and the creatures who live in them. The beauty of something quite so rare as an albino Humpback calf puts focus on the fragility of ocean life by focussing on the individual not the pod of indistinguishable humpbacks.

By looking after one we look after them all. Nothing lives in isolation.
